---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="Wayward Suns — Aryan Sidbatte"
  description="Case study: top-down action game in Unity 6 with elemental weapon combination, A* enemy AI, and a full UI/UX system."
>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-24">

    <!-- Back link -->
    <a href="/" data-cursor-scale class="inline-block text-sm text-muted hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity mb-10">
      ← Back
    </a>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary tracking-tight mb-3">Wayward Suns</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-secondary mb-5">
        Top-down action game with elemental weapon combination and enemy AI.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-5">
        {['Unity 6', 'C#', 'A*', 'Cinemachine', 'TextMesh Pro'].map(tag => (
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted border border-border bg-page px-2 py-1 rounded">
            {tag}
          </span>
        ))}
      </div>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/aryansidbatte/wayward-suns"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        data-cursor-scale
        class="text-sm text-muted hover:underline underline-offset-2 transition-all"
      >
        View on GitHub ↗
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-3">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-[1.7]">
        Top-down action game in Unity 6. You move through combat rooms, collect elemental weapons,
        and combine them into hybrid loadouts. My team shipped this over a quarter — 109 commits —
        and presented it at the CMPM 171 showcase at UC Santa Cruz.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- My role -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-3">My role</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-[1.7]">
        UI/UX engineering lead. I owned the main menu, pause menu, HUD, win/loss/credits screens,
        floating damage numbers, a full control rebinding system, scene transitions, and a greyscale
        accessibility mode.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key systems -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-6">Key systems</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-2">Weapon combination</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-[1.7]">
            6 elemental types, each with primary and secondary attacks. You carry up to 4 and merge
            them at combination stations to get hybrid loadouts.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-2">Enemy AI</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-[1.7]">
            3 types. The Lizard dashes in and retreats. The Mage keeps its distance and throws
            fireballs. The Juggernaut has 200 HP and just walks at you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-2">Navigation</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-[1.7]">
            A* pathfinding for all enemies across level geometry.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshots -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-6">Screenshots</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <img
          src="/images/wayward-suns-1.webp"
          alt="Wayward Suns gameplay screenshot"
          width="840"
          height="472"
          loading="eager"
          class="rounded-lg border border-border w-full"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/wayward-suns-2.webp"
          alt="Wayward Suns weapon station screenshot"
          width="840"
          height="472"
          loading="lazy"
          class="rounded-lg border border-border w-full"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Repo CTA -->
    <a
      href="https://github.com/aryansidbatte/wayward-suns"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      data-cursor-label="Visit"
      class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 text-sm text-secondary border border-border bg-surface hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity rounded-md"
    >
      View the repo on GitHub ↗
    </a>

  </main>
</Base>
